issue.title: LESS filter works on web but assetic:dump doesn't work
issue.body:
Hi, 

I've a less filter enabled that works ok in my website on dev environment. When I try to dump the assets for production i got the following error: 
```
[Assetic\Exception\FilterException]                         
  An error occurred while running:                            
  '/usr/bin/node' '/tmp/assetic_less6iyYJd'                   
                                                              
  Error Output:                                               
                                                              
  module.js:340                                               
      throw err;                                              
            ^                                                 
  Error: Cannot find module 'less'                            
      at Function.Module._resolveFilename (module.js:338:15)  
      at Function.Module._load (module.js:280:25)             
      at Module.require (module.js:364:17)                    
      at require (module.js:380:17)                           
      at Object.<anonymous> (/tmp/assetic_less6iyYJd:1:74)    
      at Module._compile (module.js:456:26)                   
      at Object.Module._extensions..js (module.js:474:10)     
      at Module.load (module.js:356:32)                       
      at Function.Module._load (module.js:312:12)             
      at Function.Module.runMain (module.js:497:10)   
```

The env variable NODE_PATH is not been setting properly. If I copy the content of the /tmp/assetic_less6iyYJd generated file and run it manually I got the same error: 
```
$ '/usr/bin/node' '~/assetic_less'
```
But if I set the environment variable manually it compiles ok.

I'have been haking the bundle trying to find the problem, if I comment the following line it works ok:
```php
// /vendor/kriswallsmith/assetic/src/Assetic/Filter/BaseNodeFilter.php
    protected function createProcessBuilder(array $arguments = array())
    {
        $pb = parent::createProcessBuilder($arguments);

        if ($this->nodePaths) {
            $pb->setEnv('NODE_PATH', implode(':', $this->nodePaths));
            //$this->mergeEnv($pb);
        }

        return $pb;
    }
```

SO: Ubuntu Server 14.04 x64
Node.js installed via ppa:chris-lea/node.js
Less installed on /var/www/node_modules
Symfony project on /var/www/

Config yml:
```
assetic:
    debug:          "%kernel.debug%"
    use_controller: false
    node:           "%assetic_node%"
    node_paths:     ["%kernel.root_dir%/../node_modules"]
    bundles:        []
    filters:
        cssrewrite:
            apply_to: "\.css$|\.less$"
        less:
            apply_to: "\.less$"
```

comment.body:
This is the user's NODE_PATH:
```
$ echo $NODE_PATH
/usr/lib/nodejs:/usr/lib/node_modules:/usr/share/javascript
```

issue.title: InstallerBundle: requirements translation missing
issue.body:
I got the following installation requirements without translation:

```
sylius.settings
sylius.settings.timezone_deprecated
sylius.extensions
sylius.extensions.accelerator
sylius.filesystem
sylius.filesystem.cache
sylius.filesystem.cache.help
sylius.filesystem.logs
sylius.filesystem.logs.help
sylius.filesystem.parameters
```

comment.body:
I got it, I'm using spanish locale (es).

The following file is /Resources/translations/requirements.es.yml has 2 spaces indentation and this block:

```yml
filesystem:
    0: sistema de ficheros
    cache:
      0: cache
      help:
        To set permissions run: 'sudo setfacl -R -m u:www-data:rwX -m u:`whoami`:rwX %path% & sudo setfacl -dR -m u:www-data:rwx -m u:`whoami`:rwx %path%'
    exists: Existe
    logs:
      0: logs
      help:
        To set permissions run: 'sudo setfacl -R -m u:www-data:rwX -m u:`whoami`:rwX %path% & sudo setfacl -dR -m u:www-data:rwx -m u:`whoami`:rwx %path%'
    not_exists: No existe
    not_writable: Sin permisos de escritura
    parameters:
      0: parameters.yml
      help:
        To set permissions run: 'sudo chmod a+w %path%'
    vendors: Vendors
    writable: Con permisos de escritura
```
should be:
```yml
    filesystem:
        0: sistema de ficheros
        cache:
            0: cache
            help: Para establecer los permisos ejecute: sudo setfacl -R -m u:www-data:rwX -m u:`whoami`:rwX %path% & sudo setfacl -dR -m u:www-data:rwx -m u:`whoami`:rwx %path%
        exists: Existe
        logs:
            0: logs
            help: Para establecer los permisos ejecute: sudo setfacl -R -m u:www-data:rwX -m u:`whoami`:rwX %path% & sudo setfacl -dR -m u:www-data:rwx -m u:`whoami`:rwx %path%
        not_exists: No existe
        not_writable: Sin permisos de escritura
        parameters:
            0: parameters.yml
            help: Para establecer los permisos ejecute: 'sudo chmod a+w %path%'
        vendors: Vendors
        writable: Con permisos de escritura
```
